<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-421-053  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 421 053.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Wall Street Computer Review  Sept 1990 v7 n12 p47(8).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Ergonomic design improves trading style. (includes related articleon video display terminal radiation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Kulkosky, Victor.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Designers of trading rooms are taking ergonomics into account toensure traders' more efficient functioning in the workplace.andP;  Ofenvironmental factors, lighting is one of the most important sinceeyestrain from usage of video display terminals (VDTs) is one ofthe major health problems of office workers.andP;  Another ergonomicfactor is sound and, although trading rooms are always noisy, theycan be designed so that workers can communicate easily.andP;  Chairdesign is also of importance since chronic lower back pain istraceable to chairs that do not provide good support.andP;  Desk designand desktop space are also issues and recent technologicaldevelopments offer single keyboards that can switch betweenseveral monitors and icon-driven workstation screens that becomeinterchangeable for different users.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     ErgonomicsStock MarketWork EnvironmentFurnitureMedical IssuesLightingNoise.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>